<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>blue coats • bluecoat boys</xh5><p> <i>blue coats—</i>1. <i>(coll.)</i> the police: One of the <u>blue coats</u> would attempt to put back the crowd. 2. blue-coated seamen: These were <u>blue coats</u>—French—who were on shore for a visit. 3. <i>(U.S. hist.)</i> a soldier in the Federal army during the Civil War: Wait until the States are restored and the “<u>Blue Coats</u>” are out of the way.</p><p> <i>bluecoat boys</i>—(UK hist.) schoolboys of a charity school who wear blue coats <i>(also: blue boys):</i> The day after Christmas Day was a high day with us as <u>Bluecoat boys</u>. We then received our yearly new coat and cap...</p> </entry>
